This paper deals with interference suppression techniques in heterogeneous cloud radio access networks, which involves the intersection of several computer science sub-disciplines. The most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as the paper focuses on developing strategies to enhance spectral and energy efficiencies in H-CRANs. The paper also deals with optimization models and convex optimization, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with system capacities and performance metrics, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also deals with beamforming, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper deals with collaborative processing and cooperative radio resource allocation, which falls under the category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
